text.__SUMMARY__: Conus admirationis is a species of sea snail, a marine gastropod mollusk in the family Conidae, the cone snails, cone shells or cones.These snails are predatory and venomous. They are capable of "stinging" humans.
text.Description: The length  of the shell attains 60 mm.
text.Distribution: This marine species of cone snail is endemic to the  Philippines and occurs off the Sulu Island
text.References: Poppe G.T. & Tagaro S.P. (2015). A spectacular new Conus (Conidae) from the Philippines. Visaya. 4(4): 71-75
